title: Just another day for Australian teen who pulls out snake from under car - World | The Star Online
text:
CANBERRA: For this 14-year-old Australian boy, extracting a snake from under a car before school is all in a day's work.
The boy, identified by Australian media as Oli Wardrope, is shown tussling with a carpet python in a video that has gone viral, with more than 170,000 views and 1,000 shares.
The 1min 9sec video was posted on Facebook by a Yogi McDougall on Wednesday
"Oli the snake boy wrangles a carpet snake caught up under a Cruiser before going to school," reads the caption.
The video shows Oli lying under a vehicle with part of a snake on him. A man assisting him holds on to the reptile's tail.
Oli struggles shortly before managing to get the snake loose, holding on tightly behind its head with a gloved hand.
The snake is then placed in a bag.
It is not the first snake encounter for Oli, who is from Seventeen Seventy, a town in Australia's Queensland state.
Oli's father, Chazza Wardrope, wrote on the Facebook post: "That's my boy! Been wrangling snakes since he was five!"
He added that it was "just a morning before school for him". â€“ The Straits Times/Asia News Network
